	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories El-Arish - Egyptian officials say the country has opened its border with the Gaza Strip for the first time this year. The two officials said on Wednesday the Rafah crossing point would operate for three days on a humanitarian basis. Both spoke on condition of anonymity because they weren't authorised to brief the media. The Palestinian embassy in Cairo confirmed the opening of Gaza's main gateway to the outside world. Thousands of Gaza residents are on travel lists - most of them medical patients, students and holders of residency permits of other countries. Only a few thousand will make it out in the time allotted. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news from around the continent
